org.urbanbyte.cueserver

Interface CueServerClient

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    HttpCueServerClient

    public interface CueServerClient
    The CueServerClient facilitates interaction with a CueServer. Clients have the ability to retrieve state related information, and send commands to a CueServer.

    author: Chris Reising

      • getOutputLevels

        java.lang.Integer[] getOutputLevels()
        Gets the current output levels.
        Returns:
        The current output levels between [0, 255]. The array will always contain a full DMX universe. This method will return null if there was an error communicating with the CueServer.

      • playCue

        void playCue(double cueNumber)
        Executes the given cue number on Playback.PLAYBACK_1.
        Parameters:
        cueNumber - The cue number to execute. The CueServer only supports up to one decimal place for cue number (e.g., 10.1). Any values greater than one decimal place will be truncated
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if cueNumber is not positive.

        playback - the playback to execute the cue on.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if cueNumber is not positive.

      • setChannel

        void setChannel(int channel,
                int value)
        Sets the given channel to a level on Playback.PLAYBACK_1 using a time of 0.
        Parameters:
        channel - The channel to set. Must be within [1, 512].
        value - The value of the channel level. Must be within [0, 255].
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if any argument is out of bounds.

      • setChannel

        void setChannel(int channel,
                int value,
                double timeSeconds)
        Sets the given channel to a level on Playback.PLAYBACK_1 using the provided time.
        Parameters:
        channel - The channel to set. Must be within [1, 512].
        value - The value of the channel level. Must be within [0, 255].
        timeSeconds - The time in seconds for the channel to complete its transition. Must be within [0, 65000]. The precision is up to a tenth of a second.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if any argument is out of bounds.

      • setChannel

        void setChannel(int channel,
                int value,
                double timeSeconds,
                Playback playback)
        Sets the given channel to a level on the provided playback and using the provided time.
        Parameters:
        channel - The channel to set. Must be within [1, 512].
        value - The value of the channel level. Must be within [0, 255].
        timeSeconds - The time in seconds for the channel to complete its transition. Must be within [0, 65000]. The precision is up to a tenth of a second.
        playback - the playback controlling the channel.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if any argument is out of its bounds.
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if playback is null.

      • recordCue

        void recordCue(double cueNumber,
               double uptimeSecs,
               double downtimeSecs)
        Records a cue.
        Parameters:
        cueNumber - the cue number to record. Must be positive. The CueServer only supports up to one decimal place for cue number (e.g., 10.1). The value passed in will be truncated to accommodate this.
        uptimeSecs - the fade's uptime in seconds. Must be within [0, 65000]. The precision is up to a tenth of a second.
        downtimeSecs - the fade's downtime in seconds. Must be within [0, 65000]. The precision is up to a tenth of a second.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if any argument is out of bounds.

        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if cueNumber is not positive.
